{
  "texts": [
    "Deep learning (DL) algorithms, supported by big-data techniques, have become an effective tool for identifying and recognizing cardiac disease in order to get around these restrictions.",
    "In many different fields, including image classification, computer vision, object localization, electroencephalogram (EEG) signal classification for brain-computer interfaces, and physics-informed neural networks, among others 6, DL algorithms have achieved remarkable success.",
    "They can automatically extract non-linear and hierarchical features from large datasets 7.",
    "We may be able to increase the reliability and accuracy of cardiac disease detection and",
    "Heart disease is one of the primary reasons for mortality worldwide."
  ]
}